Warren County Courthouse is a historic county courthouse located at Warren, Warren County, Pennsylvania.  It was built in 1876â€“1877, and is a -story, brick and sandstone building in the Second Empire style. It has a slate covered mansard roof. It measures 72 feet by 122 feet, and has a large 4-sided dome topped by a square clock tower and statue of justice.
It was designed by architect Milton Earl Beebe.
It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1976.
